.TH RECORDING "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
recording \- Recording menu for screen and audio capture
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B recording
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B recording
is a script providing a menu interface for recording screen, audio, and webcam. It supports various recording modes and output formats.
.PP
The script provides shortcuts for common recording tasks and can be integrated with desktop menus.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-term
Open in a terminal window
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B recording
Launch interactive recording menu
.TP
.B recording screen
Start screen recording
.TP
.B recording audio
Start audio-only recording
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/recording/settings.conf
User configuration file for recording preferences
.TP
.B ~/Videos/Recordings
Default output directory for recordings
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
Required command (ffmpeg, etc.) not found
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Supports screen, audio, and webcam recording
.IP \(bu 2
Multiple output formats supported
.IP \(bu 2
Uses ffmpeg for encoding
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B Required:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
ffmpeg - For encoding
.IP \(bu 2
pulseaudio or pipewire - For audio capture
.RE
.TP
.B Optional:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
slop - For region selection
.IP \(bu 2
dmenu or rofi - For menu interface
.RE
